Author: Max Welz [aut, cre] (<https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2945-1860>), Andreas Alfons [aut] (<https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2513-3788>)
Maintainer: Max Welz <max.welz@uzh.ch>    
Description: Implements the methodology proposed in the working paper <doi:10.48550/arXiv.2303.07167> to estimate the onset of careless responding (or a lack thereof) on the respondent-level. As a building block, nonparametric methods for chanhepoint detection in univariate and multivariate time series are also implemented in fast and efficient C++ code. The package furthermore features methods for plotting and accessor functions to extract relevant results. 
Depends: ggplot2, keras
Imports: Rcpp (>= 1.0.10), stats, parallel, tensorflow, reticulate, rlang
License: GPL (>= 3)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppEigen
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
